There is also excessive mucus accumulation in the CF intestine , and inappropriate inflammation is common [ 12 ] .
Mucus is involved in obstruction of the gut which occurs frequently in CF infants ( called meconium ileus , MI ) and adults ( called distal intestinal obstruction syndrome , DIOS ) [ 11,13 ] .
