CF mice on the mixed background have less intestinal mucus accumulation .
The most striking histological difference in the CF mouse small intestine is the accumulation of mucus in intestinal crypts which is associated with the lethal obstruction that results in death of these mice on a standard solid chow diet [ 32 ] .
